<h1>Kendall Giles</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.kendallgiles.com/now/">kendallgiles.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Appomattox
VA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Professor, Data Analyst, and Software Engineer at Orion's Arrow, Inc.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
Each day there is a new problem to solve, a new mountain to climb, and a new song to sing.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
The pursuit of interesting projects, people, and passions is my Achilles’ heel. I just don't feel right--physically, mentally, spiritually--if I'm not learning, creating, and doing. Time is short--best make the most of it.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
It’s never too late to start a new project, pursue a dream, or do something meaningful. Start right now.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Creativity, Inc.: Overcoming the Unseen Forces That Stand in the Way of True Inspiration, by Ed Catmull
</p>

